[h4 id=WhereToAccessDipswitchesInBizhawk 
	"Where to Access Dipswitches in Bizhawk
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Game options for most arcade games are changed through Dipswitches which are manual electric switches.  Some games have an in game menu that can change settings however.   
	$LF
	"To change dipswitch settings for a game in Bizhawk, 
	$LF
]div
[ol 
	[li 
		"Load the game 
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"Look at the top Bizhawk Menu Select Arcade -> Settings.  
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"After making changes you should Reboot the core.  Reboot the core by selecting Emulation -> Reboot Core. 
		$LF
	]li
]ol
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Forum/21792/bizhawk_mame_tutorial/Arcade-Settings-aka-Dipswitches.jpg 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Forum/21792/bizhawk_mame_tutorial/Karnov-dipswitch-settings.jpg 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Forum/21792/bizhawk_mame_tutorial/reboot-core.jpg 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=ArcadeInputs 
	"Arcade Inputs
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"In BizHawk go to Config-> Controllers.
	$LF
	"For Arcade games most require Coin inputs, then after inputting the number of coins the game needs to run an additional start button is needed. Coin and Start can be found on the Console tab.
	$LF
	"To map the other buttons select the relevant player.  
	$LF
	"The number and type of controls can vary depending on the game. Buttons, analog controls, lightguns, and some games have up to 5 players. 
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Forum/21792/bizhawk_mame_tutorial/bizhawk-controller-in-menu.jpg 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Forum/21792/bizhawk_mame_tutorial/Mame-normal-controls.jpg 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Forum/21792/bizhawk_mame_tutorial/Mame-player-1-controls.jpg 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=RamSearchAndRamWatch 
	"Ram Search and Ram Watch
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"Ram Search (Tools->Ram Search) and Ram Watch (Tools -> Ram Watch) work as well. For the Memory Domains use the RAM domains. The SystemBus can cause de-syncs just by searching and reading the values so avoid this.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Available Memory Domains will depend on the game. 
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[a href=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9pM1kG5uorA rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"Tutorial for Ram Search
	]a
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Forum/21792/bizhawk_mame_tutorial/Ram-Search-karnov-example.jpg 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=Tastudio 
	"TAStudio
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"In the input roll "C" is for coin and the "s" is usually the service button which might lead to other options depending on the game.  Emulated machines with a lot of different inputs may have "!" for inputs.  To find what those are it is necessary to test them.  Robotron 2084 is an arcade game example where lots of "!" inputs would need to be tested for functionality.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Forum/21792/bizhawk_mame_tutorial/Robotron-2084-undetermined-button-inputs.jpg 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"To hide specific players like Player 2 inputs, in the TAStudio window select "Show Columns" then deselect the "Show Player 2" for example.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Forum/21792/bizhawk_mame_tutorial/tastudio-toggle-showplayer2.jpg 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Arcade games will not show lag frames with the red coloring in TAStudio. To change the frame's color a LUA script will be needed. 
	$LF
	"Open up LuaConsole by Tools-> LuaConsole. 
	$LF
	"A script will need to be added to list and made active.  You can tell if the script is active if the green play icon is displayed next to the script name. 
	$LF
	"The script needs an address that changes based on whether or not the game is accepting input. This is something game dependent.  
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"A ManualSetLag Script can be downloaded from the link below. Just change the address on line 15 in the memory byte read. This script currently only works with Karnov so make sure to input an address that works for your game. 
	$LF
	[a href=https://tasvideos.org/UserFiles/Info/638459887754146781 rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"https://tasvideos.org/UserFiles/Info/638459887754146781
	]a
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		"Original script is from feos AKA vadosnaprimer 
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Forum/21792/bizhawk_mame_tutorial/bizhawk-lua-console-menu.jpg 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Forum/21792/bizhawk_mame_tutorial/Running-Manual-Set-Lag.jpg 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		[a href=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AzDjBO7_fWk rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"Introduction to TAStudio
		]a
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		[a href=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KUj4j0le6x8 rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"Introduction tutorial for Lua
		]a
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		[a href=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=N0D-OogDJOI rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"Tutorial for the Lua Console
		]a
		$LF
	]li
